Text: You hear that alarm or whatever last night? What was that? 3am
I didn’t hear that! Was it outside like someone’s car?
I’m glad the elevator seems to be working.

It was coming from indoors. Felt like it was coming from internal building speakers within our unit but was not a fire alarm. Almost sounded like someone was pressing the front door buzzer and that was triggering it bc the noise wasn’t steady but fuckin so loud. Maybe only our unit I thought it was everyone. Also the front entrance door seems more smashed up and lock feels loose
And the keys are still in this in the lobby
Piecing together the clues haha but it sucked man it was so loud and no one but us heard it
I’m sorry but also glad I didn’t hear it!
haha same! Well let me know if the front door seems off when you head out next or if it looks like someone was messing with it. I don’t love how easy it is to break in downstairs
I will pay attention. There’s sometimes a lot of crumpled up paper in the entrance as if a homeless person might have made a bed and slept there.
Ok cool well enjoy your Friday and weekend and talk soon
The handle is extra jiggly. Like it’s been yanked. But the frame and door and lock don’t seem less secure to me.
Haha I’m documenting it all. Something fishy

Hi Ryan, 

Steve here, your neighbor. 

We have to apologize for not notifying you as a courtesy earlier, but we had to move quick on leasing our condo to a young couple who started living in 4D October 1st. 

We worked with Juliana Martell (5th floor owner) to find,and fully vet, tenants and feel great with the neighbors you now have. 

We have also notified Karen who oversees the HOA from a property management perspective, so we should be in check with he terms of the HOA bylaws. 

We failed to notify you and you've likely realized you have new neighbors. Anyway, it was a pleasure meeting you and wish all the best. We now live in Florida of all places but are enjoying it. 

Should you have any issues or complaints regarding our tenants (Ethan and Katie), please let us know 

Steve & Melissa

Hi Steve! Thanks for letting me know. I met Katie’s family as they were moving in and I was worried about what happened to my neighbors but I’m glad you guys are well. Great meeting you as well. Say hi to Lucy for me.
You got it! Apologies again we didn’t notify you and provide the heads up
All happened so quick but should have let you know
